</taxonomicName>
), due to its similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FB17B0615C4E7512" authority="(Staudinger, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compararia">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FB17B06158B97528" box="[1266,1436,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. compararia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FF7BB0045C477512" author="Staudinger, O." box="[158,354,860,885]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" pagination="241 - 296" refId="ref12079" refString="Staudinger, O. (1894) Neue Lepidopteren-Arten und Varietaten aus dem palaarktischen Faunengebiet. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 7, 241 - 296." type="journal article" year="1894">Staudinger, 1894</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FE92B0045F297512" author="Wehrli, E." box="[375,524,860,885]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" refId="ref12261" refString="Wehrli, E. (1939 - 1954) Die Spanner des Palaearktischen faunengebietes. In: Seitz, A. (Ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Vol. 4. Supplement. A. Kernen, Stuttgart. pp. 254 - 766." type="book" year="1939">Wehrli (1939</bibRefCitation>
–1954), in the absence of material, treated 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FC0AB00459557512" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[1007,1136,860,885]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FC0AB00459557512" box="[1007,1136,860,885]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
putatively valid at species level, as did 
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FEC1B0275CE075FF" author="Scoble, M. J." box="[292,453,895,920]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" refId="ref11947" refString="Scoble, M. J. (Ed.) (1999) Geometrid Moths of the World: a Catalogue (Lepidoptera, Geometridae). CSIRO Publishing, Collingwood, 1016 pp. [+ Index 129 pp.]" type="book" year="1999">Scoble (1999)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B6D3C412E2CC939FF22B0FC5C12730A" blockId="14.[151,1436,751,1856]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">
If 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF05B0FC5CF075DA" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[224,469,932,957]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF05B0FC5CF075DA" box="[224,469,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hemithea squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonged to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FD32B0FC5E0D75DA" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1822" box="[727,808,932,957]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FD32B0FC5E0D75DA" box="[727,808,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hylaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in theory it could be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FB39B0FD58B075DA" authorityName="Sihvonen &amp; Skou &amp; Flamigni &amp; Fiumi &amp; Hausmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[1244,1429,932,957]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediterranea">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FB39B0FD58B075DA" box="[1244,1429,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. mediterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF72B09F5CA87587" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[151,397,967,992]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF72B09F5CA87587" box="[151,397,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hemithea squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has rather straight and well developed forewing medial lines, and the hindwing postmedial line is clearly curved (
<figureCitation id="D3E920C42E2CC939FE41B0B45F327262" box="[420,535,1004,1029]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1398,1420]" captionTargetBox="[183,1386,187,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-357@4.[172,1404,187,1386]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Adults of the Palaearctic Hylaea fasciaria species group. 1a. Hylaea fasciaria (L.) male, 13.vi.1987, Volsk, Saratov Region, South East Russia (coll. Skou). 1b. H. fasciaria male, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll Skou). 1c. H. fasciaria male, 1.viii.1972, Byerum, Öland, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1d. H. fasciaria male, 18.vii.1970, Dueodde, Bornholm, Denmark (coll. Skou). 1e. H. fasciaria flavella (Wehrli), type, original illustration from Wehrli (1939–1954, plate 24: g), Armenia, without date (coll. unknown). 1f. H. fasciaria female, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1g. H. fasciaria female, 29.vii.2000, Terre Rouge, Briancon, Dept. Hautes Alpes, France (coll. Skou). 1h. H. fasciaria cedricola (Wehrli) male, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1i. H. fasciaria cedricola female, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1j. H. fasciaria male, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1k. H. fasciaria male, 10.vi.2010, Mount Parnassos, 1650 m, Greece (coll. Skou). 1l. H. fasciaria female, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1m. H. fasciaria female, 28.vi.1981, Karpenision, Aetolia, Greece (coll. Skou). 2a. Hylaea mediterranea new species male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), holotype. 2b H. mediterranea male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2c. H. mediterranea female, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2d. H. mediterranea female, 5.vi.2005, Castelbuono, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 3a. Hylaea pinicolaria (Bellier) male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3b. H. pinicolaria male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3c. H. pinicolaria male, 6.vii.1951, La Foce, Vizzavona, Corsica, France (coll. Herbulot, coll. ZSM). 3d. H. pinicolaria female, 23.vi.1994, Haut Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 4a. Hylaea compararia (Staud.) male, 23.vi.1911, Blida, Glacieres, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4b. Hylaea compararia female, 13.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4c. Hylaea compararia female, 15.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 5a. Hemithea squalidaria O. G. Costa, original illustration from O. G. Costa, [1848]. Illustration is reproduced under a licence from the Picture Library of the Natural History Museum, London, UK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909660/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Figure 5a</figureCitation>
), whereas the forewing antemedial line is curved towards the costa and the hindwing postmedial line is only slightly curved in 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FCC7B7495EC1724F" authorityName="Sihvonen &amp; Skou &amp; Flamigni &amp; Fiumi &amp; Hausmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[802,996,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediterranea">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FCC7B7495EC1724F" box="[802,996,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. mediterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="D3E920C42E2CC939FC19B7575957724F" box="[1020,1138,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1398,1420]" captionTargetBox="[183,1386,187,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-357@4.[172,1404,187,1386]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Adults of the Palaearctic Hylaea fasciaria species group. 1a. Hylaea fasciaria (L.) male, 13.vi.1987, Volsk, Saratov Region, South East Russia (coll. Skou). 1b. H. fasciaria male, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll Skou). 1c. H. fasciaria male, 1.viii.1972, Byerum, Öland, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1d. H. fasciaria male, 18.vii.1970, Dueodde, Bornholm, Denmark (coll. Skou). 1e. H. fasciaria flavella (Wehrli), type, original illustration from Wehrli (1939–1954, plate 24: g), Armenia, without date (coll. unknown). 1f. H. fasciaria female, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1g. H. fasciaria female, 29.vii.2000, Terre Rouge, Briancon, Dept. Hautes Alpes, France (coll. Skou). 1h. H. fasciaria cedricola (Wehrli) male, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1i. H. fasciaria cedricola female, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1j. H. fasciaria male, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1k. H. fasciaria male, 10.vi.2010, Mount Parnassos, 1650 m, Greece (coll. Skou). 1l. H. fasciaria female, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1m. H. fasciaria female, 28.vi.1981, Karpenision, Aetolia, Greece (coll. Skou). 2a. Hylaea mediterranea new species male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), holotype. 2b H. mediterranea male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2c. H. mediterranea female, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2d. H. mediterranea female, 5.vi.2005, Castelbuono, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 3a. Hylaea pinicolaria (Bellier) male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3b. H. pinicolaria male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3c. H. pinicolaria male, 6.vii.1951, La Foce, Vizzavona, Corsica, France (coll. Herbulot, coll. ZSM). 3d. H. pinicolaria female, 23.vi.1994, Haut Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 4a. Hylaea compararia (Staud.) male, 23.vi.1911, Blida, Glacieres, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4b. Hylaea compararia female, 13.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4c. Hylaea compararia female, 15.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 5a. Hemithea squalidaria O. G. Costa, original illustration from O. G. Costa, [1848]. Illustration is reproduced under a licence from the Picture Library of the Natural History Museum, London, UK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909660/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Figures 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D3E920C42E2CC939FB62B75759B2724F" box="[1159,1175,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1100,1122]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,201,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-391@5.[151,1435,201,1061]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. An overview of diagnostic characters in the Palaearctic Hylaea fasciaria species group. Figure 6. H. fasciaria (Linnaeus) (Denmark, 27.vi.1977). Figure 7. H. mediterranea, new species (Italy, Sicily, 5.vi.2005, paratype). Figure 8. H. pinicolaria (Bellier) (France, Corsica, 20.-21.vii.2004). Figure 9. H. compararia (Staudinger) (Algeria, 23.vi.1911)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909662/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">7</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FB53B7575875724F" author="Costa, O. G." box="[1206,1360,1039,1064]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" pagination="419 - 422" refId="ref10720" refString="Costa, O. G. [1848] Lepidotteri. Geometre. Fauna del Regno di Napoli, 1 - 314 [1836], 315 - 370 [1848], 371 - 402 [1849], 403 - 418 [1850], 419 - 422 [1849]." type="journal article" year="1848">Costa (1848)</bibRefCitation>
gives 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF72B76C5C3D722A" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[151,280,1076,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF72B76C5C3D722A" box="[151,280,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s wingspan as 13 linee, which is 
<quantity id="8C2A91A42E2CC939FD75B76C5FCB722C" box="[656,750,1076,1101]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.33" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" unit="cm" value="2.33">2.33 cm</quantity>
, assuming he used the old Sicilian definition of line, one line being equal to 1/12 of an Sicilian ounce. Costa also reported the same wingspan for 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FB44B70F5C4172F2" authority="(Fabricius, 1787)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Thetidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FB44B70F58B97217" box="[1185,1436,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Thetidia smaragdaria</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1787)
</taxonomicName>
, which is generally smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FCF6B7245E4172F2" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1822" box="[787,868,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FCF6B7245E4172F2" box="[787,868,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hylaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens. Further, the specimen has simple (fasciculate?) antennas and long labial palpi, thus different from 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FC60B7C75EF372DF" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1822" box="[901,982,1183,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FC60B7C75EF372DF" box="[901,982,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hylaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(males). Therefore, in our opinion, the original hand-drawn illustration 
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FDE6B79C5FE172BA" box="[515,708,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">
of 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FDC5B79D5FE172BA" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[544,708,1220,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">H. squalidaria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and the description of the taxon reported in Costa's text (e.g. the wingspan of ca. 
<quantity id="8C2A91A42E2CC939FEB7B7BF5C817367" box="[338,420,1255,1280]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
) exclude the possibility of 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FD3FB7BF5EF57367" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[730,976,1255,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FD3FB7BF5EF57367" box="[730,976,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hemithea squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FB04B7B158B97367" authorityName="Sihvonen &amp; Skou &amp; Flamigni &amp; Fiumi &amp; Hausmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[1249,1436,1255,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediterranea">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FB04B7B158B97367" box="[1249,1436,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. mediterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(smallest 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FEE3B6555CE67342" authorityName="Sihvonen &amp; Skou &amp; Flamigni &amp; Fiumi &amp; Hausmann" authorityYear="2014" box="[262,451,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediterranea">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FEE3B6555CE67342" box="[262,451,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. mediterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male available to us has a wingspan of 
<quantity id="8C2A91A42E2CC939FC45B6545ED07344" box="[928,1013,1292,1317]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" unit="mm" value="31.0">31 mm</quantity>
, smallest female is 
<quantity id="8C2A91A42E2CC939FB3BB65458137342" box="[1246,1334,1292,1317]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
). 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FAAEB6545C397320" baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compararia">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FAAEB6545C397320" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hylaea compararia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FEB7B6695CFD732F" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[338,472,1327,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FEB7B6695CFD732F" box="[338,472,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. fasciaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are externally different and, according to the current knowledge, they do not occur in southern 
<collectingCountry id="33C57CD12E2CC939FF1BB60C5C16730A" box="[254,307,1364,1389]" name="Italy" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03C86FCA2E2CC939FF22B62F5E5F73B0" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" type="description">
<paragraph id="4B6D3C412E2CC939FF22B62F5E5F73B0" blockId="14.[151,1436,751,1856]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">
Based on the illustration (reprinted in 
<figureCitation id="D3E920C42E2CC939FD92B62F5FC073F7" box="[631,741,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1398,1420]" captionTargetBox="[183,1386,187,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-357@4.[172,1404,187,1386]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Adults of the Palaearctic Hylaea fasciaria species group. 1a. Hylaea fasciaria (L.) male, 13.vi.1987, Volsk, Saratov Region, South East Russia (coll. Skou). 1b. H. fasciaria male, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll Skou). 1c. H. fasciaria male, 1.viii.1972, Byerum, Öland, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1d. H. fasciaria male, 18.vii.1970, Dueodde, Bornholm, Denmark (coll. Skou). 1e. H. fasciaria flavella (Wehrli), type, original illustration from Wehrli (1939–1954, plate 24: g), Armenia, without date (coll. unknown). 1f. H. fasciaria female, 6.vii.1972, Skanør, Falsterbo, Skåne, Sweden (coll. Skou). 1g. H. fasciaria female, 29.vii.2000, Terre Rouge, Briancon, Dept. Hautes Alpes, France (coll. Skou). 1h. H. fasciaria cedricola (Wehrli) male, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1i. H. fasciaria cedricola female, ex ovo, Bey Dağlari, Antalya, Turkey (coll. Müller). 1j. H. fasciaria male, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1k. H. fasciaria male, 10.vi.2010, Mount Parnassos, 1650 m, Greece (coll. Skou). 1l. H. fasciaria female, 27–28.vii.1983, Vorarlberg, 1500 m, Austria (coll. Skou). 1m. H. fasciaria female, 28.vi.1981, Karpenision, Aetolia, Greece (coll. Skou). 2a. Hylaea mediterranea new species male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), holotype. 2b H. mediterranea male, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2c. H. mediterranea female, 9–10.x.2010, Pizzo della Rondine, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 2d. H. mediterranea female, 5.vi.2005, Castelbuono, Sicily, Italy (coll. Skou), paratype. 3a. Hylaea pinicolaria (Bellier) male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3b. H. pinicolaria male, 20–21.vii.2004, Camping Monte Cinto, Haut-Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 3c. H. pinicolaria male, 6.vii.1951, La Foce, Vizzavona, Corsica, France (coll. Herbulot, coll. ZSM). 3d. H. pinicolaria female, 23.vi.1994, Haut Asco, Corsica, France (coll. Skou). 4a. Hylaea compararia (Staud.) male, 23.vi.1911, Blida, Glacieres, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4b. Hylaea compararia female, 13.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 4c. Hylaea compararia female, 15.ix.1911, Glacieres, Blida, Algeria (coll. BMNH). 5a. Hemithea squalidaria O. G. Costa, original illustration from O. G. Costa, [1848]. Illustration is reproduced under a licence from the Picture Library of the Natural History Museum, London, UK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4909660" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4909660/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Figure 5a</figureCitation>
), we are unable to exclude the possibility that 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FB12B62158B973F7" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[1271,1436,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FB12B62158B973F7" box="[1271,1436,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be a species of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FDC6B6C45F9273D2" box="[547,695,1436,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
. There are potentially several 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FBEAB6C4598573D2" box="[1039,1184,1436,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
species, which live at the sea-level in southern 
<collectingCountry id="33C57CD12E2CC939FE4AB6E75CC773BF" box="[431,482,1471,1496]" name="Italy" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Italy</collectingCountry>
that may be relevant in this context.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03C86FCA2E2CC939FF22B6BD5C3E7127" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="4B6D3C412E2CC939FF22B6BD5C3E7127" blockId="14.[151,1436,751,1856]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF22B6BD5C4F739A" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[199,362,1508,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF22B6BD5C4F739A" box="[199,362,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">H. squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Oronzo Gabriele Costa, the father of Achille Costa, and it is possible that the type specimen(s) of the taxon no longer exist. 
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FD79B55F5E157047" author="Turati, E." box="[668,816,1543,1568]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref12106" refString="Turati, E. (1911) Lepidotteri del Museo Zoologico Universit della R. di Napoli. Descrizioni Tues forme nuove e note critiche. Annuario del Museo Zoologico R. della Universit di Napoli, 3, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1911">Turati (1911)</bibRefCitation>
visited the Costa Collection in the Zoological Museum of Naples, 
<collectingCountry id="33C57CD12E2CC939FEFEB5745C6A7022" box="[283,335,1580,1605]" name="Italy" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Italy</collectingCountry>
, and he does not mention 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FD74B5745E377022" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[657,786,1580,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FD74B5745E377022" box="[657,786,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Only two wings, thorax and head with an antenna of 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF72B5175F0D700F" authority="(Costa, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[151,552,1615,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Megalycinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serraria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF72B5175CA27000" box="[151,391,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Megalycinia serraria</emphasis>
(Costa, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FDD2B5175F9F700F" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" box="[567,698,1615,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ennominae">Ennominae</taxonomicName>
) are mentioned in the article. Also 
<bibRefCitation id="2F4341B02E2CC939FBAEB51759C4700F" author="Conci, C." box="[1099,1249,1615,1640]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" pagination="817 - 1069" refId="ref10688" refString="Conci, C. (1975) Repertorio delle biografie e bibliografie degli scrittori e cultori italiani di entomologia. Memorie della Societ entomologica Italiana, 48, 817 - 1069." type="journal article" year="1975">Conci (1975)</bibRefCitation>
reports that part of the A. Costa collection is destroyed. Due to the unavailability of the type material, we are unable to place the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FF39B5CF5C7870D7" authorityName="O. G. Costa" authorityYear="1848" box="[220,349,1687,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hemithea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squalidaria">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FF39B5CF5C7870D7" box="[220,349,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">squalidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FE16B5CF5F6170D7" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1822" box="[499,580,1687,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hylaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79A6E0532E2CC939FE16B5CF5F6170D7" box="[499,580,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Hylaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We revert it to its original combination, and its taxonomic combination and status are uncertain, being potentially valid at species level and potentially belonging to another genus in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="8CD247C22E2CC939FEE8B5875CBB709F" box="[269,414,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
(see discussion above). We have been unable to trace a candidate for a 
<typeStatus id="946982E32E2CC939FB5EB5B85831709F" box="[1211,1300,1760,1784]" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">neotype</typeStatus>
designation basing on a specimen from southern 
<collectingCountry id="33C57CD12E2CC939FDA7B45C5F53717A" box="[578,630,1796,1821]" name="Italy" pageId="14" pageNumber="483">Italy</collectingCountry>
that would fit well enough the habitus of the figure from the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
